## Minimal primes of the codim-2 strata (workflow §10)

From `stage4b_minprimes.out.txt` — **all three are irreducible upstairs**:

- **SubEven** is prime (codim 7, degree 6):
  `(N4−w4, N3−w3, N2−w2, N1−w1, 4M−e1(w), u, e3(w))`.
- **SubOdd** is prime (codim 7, degree 6): same with `N1+w1`.
- **IR+IZ** is prime (codim 7, degree 192):
  `(h, q1..q4, e3(w), N1N2N3N4 + 8J² − u² − u·e2(w) + (w1w2+w1w3+w2w3)·w4²)`.

Irreducibility of `IR+IZ` means the ramification–difference intersection is a
single component upstairs; there is no hidden splitting to track through the
poset at this node.

